Canelo Alvarez Boxing Record

Canelo Alvarez is one of the most successful boxers in the world, with a record of 59 wins, 2 losses, and 2 draws. He has won titles in four weight classes, from light middleweight to light heavyweight, and is the first and only boxer in history to become undisputed champion at super middleweight.

Canelo Alvarez's Top Fights

Some of Canelo Alvarez's top fights include:

Canelo Alvarez vs. Floyd Mayweather Jr. (2013): This fight was one of the most anticipated boxing matches of all time, and it did not disappoint. Mayweather, who was considered the best pound-for-pound boxer in the world, defeated Alvarez by a majority decision.
Canelo Alvarez vs. Gennady Golovkin (2017, 2018): This was a highly competitive two-fight series between two of the best middleweights in the world. The first fight ended in a draw, and the second fight was won by Alvarez by majority decision.
Canelo Alvarez vs. Callum Smith (2020): In this fight, Alvarez unified the super middleweight titles by defeating Smith by unanimous decision.
Canelo Alvarez vs. Billy Joe Saunders (2021): In this fight, Alvarez defeated Saunders by knockout in the eighth round to become the undisputed super middleweight champion.
Canelo Alvarez vs. Caleb Plant (2021): In this fight, Alvarez defeated Plant by knockout in the 11th round to become the first undisputed champion in super middleweight history.
Canelo Alvarez is a true boxing great, and his boxing record is a testament to his skill and determination. He is sure to continue to entertain fans for years to come.
